RIYADH: Egypt on Thursday claimed a 1-0 victory over Oman in their opening match of the 2022 Arab Cup U20 at the Prince Sultan bin Abdulaziz Stadium in Abha. The evening match was part of Group D of the 18-team tournament which will run until Aug. 6. The Pharaohs took the lead through a 43rd-minute goal by Ahmed Nader, and although Oman came back strongly in the second half there would be no change in the score, with Egyptâ€™s Raafat Khalil nominated the player of the match. The result leaves Egypt as early leaders of the three-team group with three points, while Oman are bottom. Oman will next take on Somalia on Sunday before Egypt face the same opposition the following Wednesday.